Tutorial by Drew Neil
(http://vimcasts.org/episodes/synchronizing-plugins-with-git-submodules-and-pathogen/)

Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/nilspk/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule update --init

Then make two new directories
    mkdir backup
    mkdir tmp

To upgrade all submodules
    git submodule foreach git pull origin master

To ignore changes in submodules, add the line "ignore=dirty" to all
submodule entries in .gitmodules.

Windows specific configurations:
    create a folder called vimfiles in home directory
    copy autoload folder into vimfiles
    copy _vimrc into home folder
    overwrite color folder in the windows installation path for (g)vim
